<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-82-0366 </DOCNO><TEXT>We investigate the evolution of spatially homogeneous cosmological modelsclose to the initial singularity, in the distant future and at some intermediarystages. Our starting point for this investigation are the Einstein fieldequations with vacuum or perfect-fluid source. The possible asymptoticforms of the spacetime metric can be derived from approximate solutioncurves in neighbourhoods of the singular points of this system.</TEXT></DOC>